n (b. 1950)\nBULLET::::- 1992 – Max Dupain, Australian photographer and educator (b. 1911)\nBULLET::::- 1992 – Tzeni Karezi, Greek actress and screenwriter\nBULLET::::- 1993 – Reggie Lewis, American basketball player (b. 1965)\nBULLET::::- 1994 – Kevin Carter, South African photographer and journalist (b. 1960)\nBULLET::::- 1995 – Melih Esenbel, Turkish politician and diplomat, 20th Turkish Minister of Foreign Affairs (b. 1915)\nBULLET::::- 1995 – Rick Ferrell, American baseball player and coach (b. 1905)\nBULLET::::- 1995 – Miklós Rózsa, Hungarian-American composer and conductor (b. 1907)\nBULLET::::- 1998 – Binnie Barnes, English-American actress (b. 1903)\nBULLET::::- 1999 – Aleksandr Danilovich Aleksandrov, Russian mathematician, physicist, and mountaineer (b. 1912)\nBULLET::::- 1999 – Harry Edison, American trumpet player (b. 1915)\nBULLET::::- 2000 – Gordon Solie, American sportscaster (b. 1929)\nBULLET::::- 2001 – Rhonda Sing, Canadian wrestler (b. 1961)\nBULLET::::- 2001 – Leon Wilkeson, American bass player and songwriter (b. 1952)\nBULLET::::- 2003 – Vance Hartke, American lieutenant, lawyer, and politician (b. 1919)\nBULLET::::- 2003 – Bob Hope, English-American actor, comedian, television personality, and businessman (b. 1903)\nBULLET::::- 2005 – Al Held, American painter and academic (b. 1928)\nBULLET::::- 2005 – Marten Toonder, Dutch author and illustrator (b. 1912)\nBULLET::::- 2006 – Maryann Mahaffey, American academic and politician (b. 1925)\nBULLET::::- 2007 – James Oyebola, Nigerian-English boxer (b. 1961)\nBULLET::::- 2008 – Youssef Chahine, Egyptian director, producer, and screenwriter (b. 1926)\nBULLET::::- 2008 – Horst Stein, German-born Swiss conductor (b. 1928)\nBULLET::::- 2008 – Isaac Saba Raffoul, Mexican businessman (b. 1923)\nBULLET::::- 2010 – Maury Chaykin, American-Canadian actor (b. 1949)\nBULLET::::- 2010 – Jack Tatum, American football player (b. 1948)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – Norman Alden, American actor (b. 1924)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – R. G. Armstrong, American actor and playwright (b. 1917)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – Darryl Cotton, Australian singer-songwriter, guitarist, and actor (b. 1949)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – Geoffrey Hughes, English actor (b. 1944)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – Tony Martin, American actor and singer (b. 1913)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – Jack Taylor, English footballer and referee (b. 1930)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Fernando Alonso, Cuban dancer, co-founded the Cuban National Ballet (b. 1914)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Lindy Boggs, American politician and diplomat, 5th United States Ambassador to the Holy See (b. 1916)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Bud Day, American colonel and pilot, Medal of Honor recipient (b. 1925)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Kidd Kraddick, American radio host (b. 1959)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Ilya Segalovich, Russian businessman, co-founded Yandex (b. 1964)\nBULLET::::- 2014 – Richard Bolt, New Zealand air marshal and pilot (b. 1923)\nBULLET::::- 2014 – George Freese, American baseball player and coach (b. 1926)\nBULLET::::- 2014 – Wallace Jones, American basketball player and coach (b. 1926)\nBULLET::::- 2014 – Francesco Marchisano, Italian cardinal (b. 1929)\nBULLET::::- 2014 – Paul Schell, American lawyer and politician, 50th Mayor of Seattle (b. 1937)\nBULLET::::- 2015 – Rickey Grundy, American singer-songwriter (b. 1959)\nBULLET::::- 2015 – A. P. J. Abdul Kalam, Indian engineer, academic, and politician, 11th President of India (b. 1931)\nBULLET::::- 2015 – Samuel Pisar, Polish-born American lawyer and author (b. 1929)\nBULLET::::- 2015 – Anthony Shaw, English general (b. 1930)\nBULLET::::- 2016 – Einojuhani Rautavaara, Finnish composer (b.1928)\nBULLET::::- 2016 – James Alan McPherson, American short story writer and essayist (b. 1943)\nBULLET::::- 2016 – Jerry Doyle, American actor and talk show host (b. 1956)\nBULLET::::- 2016 – Piet de Jong, Dutch politician and naval officer, Minister of Defence (1963–67), Prime Minister of the Netherlands (1967–71) (b. 1915)\nBULLET::::- 2017 – Sam Shepard, American pla