(BBC Four)\n\nIn June 2013, BBC Radio 4 broadcast adaptions of \"The Drowned World\" and \"Concrete Island\" as part of a season of dystopian fiction entitled \"Dangerous Visions\".\n\nBULLET::::- Social control\nBULLET::::- Technology\nBULLET::::- Mass media\nBULLET::::- Entropy\n\nBULLET::::- Ballard, J.G. (1984). \"Empire of the Sun\". .\nBULLET::::- Ballard, J.G. (1991). \"The Kindness of Women\". .\nBULLET::::- Ballard, J.G. (1993). \"The Atrocity Exhibition\" (expanded and annotated edition). .\nBULLET::::- Ballard, J.G. (2006). \"Look back at Empire\". \"The Guardian\", 4 March 2006.\nBULLET::::- Baxter, J. (2001). \"J.G. Ballard\". \"The Literary Encyclopedia\". Retrieved 11 March 2006.\nBULLET::::- Baxter, J. (ed.) (2008). \"J.G. Ballard\", London: Continuum.\nBULLET::::- Baxter, John (2011). \"The Inner Man: The Life of J. G. Ballard.\" London: Weidenfeld & Nicolson.\nBULLET::::- Brigg, Peter (1985). \"J.G. Ballard\". Rpt. Borgo Press/Wildside Press.\nBULLET::::- Collins English Dictionary. . Quoted in Ballardian: The World of JG Ballard. Retrieved 11 March 2006.\nBULLET::::- Cowley, J. (2001). \"The Ballard of Shanghai jail\". Review of \"The Complete Stories\" by J.G. Ballard. \"The Observer\", 4 November 2001. Retrieved 11 March 2006.\nBULLET::::- Delville, Michel. \"J.G. Ballard\". Plymouth: Northcote House, 1998.\nBULLET::::- Gasiorek, A. (2005). \"J. G. Ballard\". Manchester University Press.\nBULLET::::- Hall, C. \"Extreme Metaphor: A Crash Course in the Fiction of JG Ballard\". Retrieved 11 March 2006.\nBULLET::::- Livingstone, D.B. (1996?). \"Prophet with Honour\". Retrieved 12 March 2006.\nBULLET::::- Luckhurst, R. (1998). \"The Angle Between Two Walls: The Fiction of J. G. Ballard\". Liverpool University Press.\nBULLET::::- McGrath, R. JG Ballard Book Collection. Retrieved 11 March 2006.\nBULLET::::- McGrath, Rick (ed.). \"The JG Ballard Book\". The Terminal Press. 2013.\nBULLET::::- Oramus, Dominika. \"Grave New World\". Warsaw: University of Warsaw, 2007.\nBULLET::::- Pringle, David, \"Earth is the Alien Planet: J.G. Ballard's Four-Dimensional Nightmare\", San Bernardino, CA: The Borgo Press, 1979.\nBULLET::::- Pringle, David (ed.) and Ballard, J.G. (1982). \"From Shanghai to Shepperton\". \"Re/Search\" 8/9: J.G. Ballard: 112–124. .\nBULLET::::- Rossi, Umberto (2009). \"A Little Something about Dead Astronauts\", \"Science-Fiction Studies\", No. 107, 36:1 (March), 101–120.\nBULLET::::- Stephenson, Gregory, \"Out of the Night and Into the Dream: A Thematic Study of the Fiction of J.G. Ballard\", New York: Greenwood Press, 1991.\nBULLET::::- McGrath, Rick (ed.). \"Deep Ends: The JG Ballard Anthology 2014\". The Terminal Press. 2014.\nBULLET::::- V. Vale (ed.) (2005). \"J.G. Ballard: Conversations\" (excerpts). RE/Search Publications.\nBULLET::::- V. Vale (ed.) and Ryan, Mike (ed). (2005). \"J.G. Ballard: Quotes\" (excerpts). RE/Search Publications.\nBULLET::::- J. G. Ballard's online fiction at Free Speculative Fiction Online\nBULLET::::- Ballardian (Simon Sellars)\nBULLET::::- J.G. Ballard Literary Archive & Bibliographies (Rick McGrath)\nBULLET::::- 2008 profile of J. G. Ballard by Theodore Dalrymple in \"City Journal\" magazine\nBULLET::::- J. G. Ballard Literary Estate\nBULLET::::- \"J G Ballard\" at the British Library\n\nBULLET::::- articles, reviews and essays\nBULLET::::- \"Landscapes From a Dream\", J G Ballard and modern art\nBULLET::::- The Marriage of Reason and Nightmare, \"City Journal,\" Winter 2008\nBULLET::::- \"Miracles of Life\" reviewed by Karl Miller in the Times Literary Supplement, 12 March 2008\nBULLET::::- J.G. Ballard: The Glow of the Prophet Diane Johnson article on Ballard from \"The New York Review of Books\"\nBULLET::::- Reviews of Ballard's work and John Foyster's criticism of Ballard's work featured in Edition 46 of Science Fiction magazine edited by Van Ikin.\nBULLET::::- A review of Ballard's \"Running Wild\"\n\nBULLET::::- source material\nBULLET::::- J. G. Ballard and hi